#---: Phase 29: v2 Integration Examples

Write comprehensive v2 example programs that exercise ownership, classes,
unions, protocols, generics and typedefs together. These serve as
integration tests for the full v2 feature set.

#ol:
  #*: Write #~"examples/ownership.z": comprehensive ownership scenarios
    (take, borrow, lock, swap, scope cleanup) using classes and unions.
  #*: Write #~"examples/linkedlist.z": generic linked list using classes
    and generics, demonstrating ownership of node chains.
  #*: Write #~"examples/result.z": #~"result" union type (ok/error)
    using generics, demonstrating error handling pattern.
  #*: Write #~"examples/iterator.z": iterator protocol, demonstrating
    protocol instances and dynamic dispatch.
  #*: Verify all v2 example programs compile with gcc and produce
    correct output under ASan (address sanitizer).

#---: Phase 30: Static String Literals + ZStr Header Modernization \[COMPLETE\]

Modernize the #~"ZStr" layout to a 64-bit header and add static string
support so string literals are never heap-allocated.

#ol:
  #*: #+ Replace #~"int32_t len" with #~"uint64_t size" (byte count, not
    character count). Bit 63 is the static flag; bits 62-0 store size.
    Data starts at 8-byte boundary for optimal alignment.
  #*: #+ Add #~"ZSTR_STATIC" macro for compile-time string literal
    declaration. Static strings live in #~".rodata" and are never freed.
  #*: #+ Add #~"ZSTR_SIZE", #~"ZSTR_IS_STATIC" accessor macros.
  #*: #+ Add #~"zstr_free" helper that checks the static flag before
    calling #~"free".
  #*: #+ Update emitter to collect and deduplicate string literals,
    emitting #~"ZSTR_STATIC" declarations at file scope.
  #*: #+ Plain string literals emit static references instead of
    #~"zstr_new" calls. Interpolation fragments also use static strings.
  #*: #+ Replace all #~"free(stringvar)" with #~"zstr_free(stringvar)" in
    scope cleanup, return paths, reassignment, and with-blocks.
  #*: #+ Update union destructor to use #~"zstr_free" for string subtypes.
  #*: #+ Create #~"doc/strings.pdoc" documenting ZStr layout, static flag
    semantics, and comparison with other implementations.
  #*: #+ Update tests: assertions for #~"zstr_free" instead of #~"free",
    new tests for static string deduplication, interpolation fragments,
    and ASan verification.

Files: #~"src/zemitterc.py", #~"tests/test_emitter.py",
#~"doc/strings.pdoc", #~"doc/roadmap.pdoc"

#---: Phase 31: C Runtime Library

Extract generated C helpers into a precompiled static library. Currently
the emitter inlines string handling (#~"ZStr", #~"zstr_new",
#~"zstr_cat", etc.) into every generated #~".c" file. This phase moves
runtime support code into separate source files, compiles them into a
static library (#~"libzrt.a"), and links it into the final executable.

#ol:
  #*: Create #~"runtime/" directory with #~"zrt_string.c" /
    #~"zrt_string.h": move #~"ZStr" struct, #~"zstr_new",
    #~"zstr_cat", #~"zstr_from_i64", #~"zstr_from_f64",
    #~"zstr_print" out of emitted code.
  #*: Create #~"runtime/zrt_memory.c" / #~"zrt_memory.h": wrapper
    allocators (#~"zrt_malloc", #~"zrt_free") that can later be
    swapped for arena or GC backends. Class construction and
    scope-exit cleanup call these instead of raw #~"malloc"/#~"free".
  #*: Build system: #~"Makefile" target to compile #~"runtime/*.c"
    into #~"libzrt.a" (static archive via #~"ar rcs").
  #*: Update #~"zemitterc.py": emit #~"#include \"zrt_string.h\""
    and #~"#include \"zrt_memory.h\"" instead of inlining helpers.
    Remove inline #~"ZStr" definitions from emitted code.
  #*: Update compile/link step: #~"gcc -o prog prog.c -L. -lzrt"
    (or pass #~"libzrt.a" directly).
  #*: Update all tests: #~"compile_and_run" and
    #~"compile_and_run_asan" helpers link against #~"libzrt.a".
  #*: Verify all existing examples and tests still pass with the
    library-based build.
  #*: Future runtime candidates: format/print infrastructure, I/O,
    union destructors, protocol vtable helpers, generic container
    support.

