#---: Phase 33: Developer Tools

Language server, linter, and formatter to support editing zerolang
source files in IDEs and editors.

#ol:
  #*: Language Server (LSP): implement a basic LSP server providing
    diagnostics (type errors, ownership violations), go-to-definition,
    hover (type info), and completion. Reuse #~"zparser",
    #~"ztypecheck" as the analysis backend. Communicate via
    JSON-RPC over stdio.
  #*: Linter: standalone pass over parsed AST to flag style issues,
    unused variables, unreachable code, and shadowed names. Output
    in standard diagnostic format (file:line:col: message).
  #*: Formatter: canonical source formatter that reads #~".z" files
    and rewrites them with consistent indentation, spacing, and
    line wrapping. Idempotent (running twice produces the same output).
  #*: Editor integration: VS Code extension and/or tree-sitter grammar
    for syntax highlighting. Wire LSP server into the extension.

